City Court of New York — General Term, April, 1901.

Before Fitzsimons, Oh. J., Hasoall and O’Dwyer, JJ.

Kate J. Collins, Respondent, v. Anderson Fowler, Appellant. Appeal from a judgment entered upon the report of a referee in favor of plaintiff. Weiser & Bridges (Henry Wilson Bridges, of counsel), for appellant; Howe & Hummel, for respondent. Judgment affirmed, with costs.

No opinion.
